A former Deputy Speaker, House of Representatives, Lasun Yusuf, has tendered his resignation from the All Progressives Congress (APC). Yusuf was a former gubernatorial aspirant of APC in 2018. He also aspired to be the gubernatorial candidate of the party in the party’s recently concluded primary election where he came in a distant third position behind Moshood Adeoti and the eventual winner and Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola. He submitted his resignation letter this morning at the APC Secretariat, Ogo Oluwo Osogbo. Details laters…